Title: Data-Snooping, Technical Trading Rule Performance, and the Bootstrap 
Abstract:
 In this paper we utilize White's Reality Check bootstrap methodology
 (White (1999)) to evaluate simple technical trading rules while
 quantifying the data-snooping bias and fully adjusting for its effect in
 the context of the full universe from which the trading rules were drawn.
 Hence, for the first time, the paper presents a comprehensive test of
 performance across all technical trading rules examined. We consider the
 study of Brock, Lakonishok, and LeBaron (1992), expand their universe of
 26 trading rules, apply the rules to 100 years of daily data on the Dow
 Jones Industrial Average, and determine the effects of data-snooping. Copyright The American Finance Association 1999. 
