Author-Name: Andrew Metrick 
Author-Workplace-Name: Harvard University and NBER 
Title: Performance Evaluation with Transactions Data: The Stock Selection of Investment Newsletters 
Abstract:
 This paper analyzes the equity-portfolio recommendations made by
 investment newsletters. Overall, there is no significant evidence of
 superior stock-picking ability for this sample of 153 newsletters.
 Moreover, there is no evidence of abnormal short-run performance
 persistence ("hot hands"). The comprehensive and bias-free transactions
 database also allows for insights into the precision of performance
 evaluation. Using a measure of precision defined in the paper, a
 transactions-based approach yields a median improvement of 10 percent over
 a corresponding factor model. This compares favorably with the precision
 gained by adding factors to the CAPM. Copyright The American Finance Association 1999. 
