Author-Workplace-Name: Virginia Tech,  
Author-Name: Stacey R. Nutt 
Author-Workplace-Name: Vestek Systems 
Title: Inefficiency in Analysts' Earnings Forecasts: Systematic Misreaction or Systematic Optimism? 
Abstract:
 A rational analysis of analyst behavior predicts that analysts immediately
 and without bias incorporate information into their forecasts. Several
 studies document analysts' tendency to systematically underreact to
 information. Underreaction is inconsistent with rationality. Other studies
 indicate that analysts systematically overreact to new information or that
 they are systematically optimistic. This study discriminates between these
 three hypotheses by examining the interaction between the nature of
 information and the type of reaction by analysts. The evidence indicates
 that analysts underreact to negative information, but overreact to
 positive information. These results are consistent with systematic
 optimism in response to information. Copyright The American Finance Association 1999. 
